The <b>SMART (System for the Mechanical Analysis and Retrieval of Text) Information Retrieval System</b> is an <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
information retrieval</link> system developed at <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../422/7954422.xml">
Cornell University</link></university>
 in the 1960s. Many important concepts in information retrieval were developed as part of research on the <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="ftp://ftp.cs.cornell.edu/pub/smart/">
SMART</weblink> system, including the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../134/1256134.xml">
vector space model</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../361/5818361.xml">
relevance feedback</link>.<p>

